,Recommended,492340,24720915,"Posted: 5 August, 2016",all,Paidian,"Even though it is in Early Access, the game is fun thats for sure. The art in general is quite cute and funny and the movement is simple (with only movement keys and two buttons to do everything).There are still a few problems that takes away considerable amount of fun out of the game though:1-) There is no off-side which can be exploited and weakens the experience of the game in general.2-) AI is weird and for both sides. The auto switching of the player chooses the sub-optimal targets, the enemy team freezes up and doesn't move (in friendly matches) etc.3-) Player movement. When I select a player, it keeps on moving on its own for a while and it makes you really angry when your player moves away from the ball because some AI code decided that its the best decision for the ""chosen"" player.4-) Pass button used for precise shooting. The game sometimes decides that there is a player right next to you so you should use pass option instead of shooting, even though you're literally face to face with the enemy goal keeper.There are a few other problems but all in all the game is a fun experience for those who don't want to deal with all the buttons and technicality of soccer while playing the game."
