,Recommended,492340,33921994,Posted: 31 July,all,Antagonist,"This may be a long review, so I will put it as simply as possible first, and if you choose to read the rest, that is up to you. Alright. Simply put, if you look at the videos and the screen shots for this game, and you think it looks good, you WILL enjoy it. What you see is EXACTLY what you get.Now for the longer review, and probably some rambling, to be honest.I freakin' love this game. I'm not a fan of soccer/football per se. I played as a kid, hated it. Love playing as an adult. I'm not a sports watcher at all, but I enjoy playing them in real life, and even more so in video games.You know what else I love? Charming retro graphics. I have an Nvidia GeForce GT 2GB GPU, 16 GB of RAM, i7 3.4ghz quad-core 3770 CPU. So I don't HAVE to play these retro games, I play them because they're fun. I play them because they remind me of my childhood.Okay, I know you're not reading this for my life story, I just wanted to make the point that I'm not playing this due to not being able to play something ""better"". The minute I saw this pop up in my queue I got excited. Stupidly, I bought WWE 2k17 because it was on sale. It wasn't good, you're better off getting Fire Pro World. God bless Steam and their refund policy.****THE PROS****Charming retro graphics.Easy controls.Local multiplayer, with online multiplayer either coming to this game, or as a separate game. If you get this early access, however, and they do release it as a separate game, you will get the online one for free. So if the screen shots look good to you, you're more than likely going to like this game.Absolute simplicity (in a good way). A 32 year old man like me can enjoy this game. And a 13 year old kid, like my son can enjoy this game.Different game modes. ""Friendly match"" which is exhibition in any other game. Practicing taking shots on the net. League play. And another one that's ""Coming Soon"".Charming sound and music.Some damn fun gameplay.Arcade gameplay. You can tackle someone, which in real soccer, would get you some yellow or red cards. (This is also a con)CONTROLLER SUPPORT!!! I spent too many years as a PC exclusive gamer who didn't use a controller. Get a controller. They're cheap, it'll make your PC gaming experience a lot better in general.****THE CONS****Currently no online multiplayer.Not much difference between the players appearances. They all look virtually exactly the same, with the only differences being hair color, and skin color. As far as I saw, there wasn't even different hairstyles. For an early access game that originally planned (And still states as much on their Store Page) for this game to leave Early Access before the end of 2016, that's pretty unacceptable to me.Arcade gameplay. You can tackle someone, which in real soccer, would get you some yellow or red cards. (This may also be a pro)Virtually no customizing the gameplay rules. You can't turn on fouls, etc.Absolutely no customization of players. You can't make a player. You can't make a team. These sorts of things are not difficult to add to a game like this, especially when every single player looks the same.A feeling of concern. Like I said, this games store page said it would be out of early access by the end of 2016, and we're about 3/4ths done with 2017. I love this game, so I REALLY hope it wasn't another abandoned early access. That would be very disappointing. I am going to do my best to contact the devs before I reach the 2 hour limit I have before refund. If it was abandoned, you will not be reading this, because my entire review would be changed to the same review I leave for all abandoned early access game ""Another abandoned early access turd"".***********************************************Now, with all that said, I find the pros outweigh the cons. I have only done one game upon writing this review, but that one game was a butt load of fun, if a little bit too easy. This IS the kind of game where you can play one single match, and know whether or not you like it.  Also, the game is only 10 dollars, so you're not really losing a big investment, and again, Steam offers refunds if you do not exceed 2 hours and 2 weeks. But as I've said before, if this review has not changed, it's because my feelings on the game have not changed.And one more point, if you have a friend, a family member or a girlfriend/boyfriend that you can play this game with, it will only make it that much more fun.Buying games like this is positive reinforcement for devs like the ones that made this game. If more people buy it, they're much more likely to be able to invest more into developing which means we all win. If by the time you're reading this online play has been added, please feel free to add me to friends, because I can't wait to play some people.OVERALL SCORE: 7.8 out of 10. When online comes out, 8.5 out of 10."
