76561197996610226,Recommended,492340,29084786,Posted: 7 January,all,lei07,"ReviewIn a world swamped with endless FIFA games, that are the same basic game over and over again with a fresh lick of paint, it is just a sheer joy to play a football title like this.For those that remember the Super Nintendo release day line up, this is very much a side-scrolling Super Soccer, with the mode and content diversity of ISS Deluxe. Such a good start to a game in alpha.Fun, fast and easy to play, but with challenging opponents, and just crammed with charm. The stadiums are well envisioned, and I love the pixel parodies. Sorry for the spoilers, but loading up my first game to see, no less, than Freddy Mercury, Wheres Wally/Waldo, Stan Lee, Fred Durst, a Xenomorph, and many other caricatures of well-known personalites and fictional characters.Such a fantastic start to Pixel Cup Soccer 17, retro lovers rejoice!Suggestions} As much as I love the two button NES style, making it a four button SNES style would allow for a manual tackle jump/dodge button, and an alternative tackle (sholder, push etc).} Control over the goalies kicks, a choice between a long lob and a near pass would be great.} General improvement for Keeper AI, not that it is terrible, it needs a little tweaking.} A ref sprite. Seriously, a fat referee character dressed in all black would make my day. And maybe make him distracted or sleepy at times, so you can foul when he's not looking.} Cards for bad tackles, 2 strikes a player is out (yellow then red). No other penalties though, such as offside etc.} Maybe change the menu format? I don't mind but the Mobile Phone Port look may turn people off.} Injuries and substitutions, automatically handled. A low chance per tackle of a player getting too injured to play.} Option for random weather and time conditions.} More of the same! Really is a breath of fresh air to see such a football game out there. Great initial Steam release!"
