76561198079307620,Not Recommended,492340,35263224,Posted: 28 September,all,SaintTodd,"First, I have to say, the game looks great. Art style is extremely well done.But gameplay is not quite up to snuff. They clearly were paying homage to classic arcade games, and they brought the issues those games suffered from along. The main two issues are defensive auto player switching and a complete lack of any kind of physics. Personally, I don't know anyone who actually likes auto player switching, and any game that gives the option, I think most of us would choose to turn it off. Even when the game does a good job of giving you the player you would want on defense (it does... Ok, here), it's the timing of switching that matters.On the other issue, don't get me wrong, I'm not asking for an actual physics engine. I'd simply like to see a few frames of animation when a player starts moving in the opposite direction. Just like in SWoS, defenders are able intercept passes made in front of them, while being behind the passer, then immediately start running the opposite direction with the ball. It's possibly worse here than in that game, as I'm consistently seeing the AI intercept my passes in this way, when I press the button while the defender is still several steps behind me.I think if they could marry this visual look with gameplay more similar to something like Stir Fried Games Soccer, they'd have real hit."
